            "Understand that a consonant-le is a final syllable where a consonant plus le makes a /consonant + ul/ sound",
            "Apply the consonant-le division rule: the consonant-le takes the consonant just before it",
            "Read two-syllable words ending in consonant-le (ta-ble, lit-tle, ap-ple, pur-ple)",
